        "description": {
            "value": "<p>Clockwork mechanisms tick away inside the weights of these <em>+1 striking returning bolas</em>, spooling out more cord in midair.</p>\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">1</span> Interact</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The cord of the bola snakes out as you throw it, allowing the weapon to wrap around a group of enemies. You use the bolas to attempt a ranged @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Trip] against all creatures in a @Template[type:burst|distance:5] within the weapon's first range increment. Roll a separate Athletics check for each target. Each attempt counts toward your multiple attack penalty, but don't increase your penalty until you have made all the attempts.</p>"
